	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 24th 9:32 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are correct Rishaka<br><br>It is a popular misconception that damage bonus is added to a weapon's damage ratio. This is not true.<br><br>Let's say I was using a 10 damage 20 delay weapon. with my warrior I would probably max out around 50 damage with this (just a guess). Assuming I had a 12 damage bonus on the weapon (again, just a guess) I would do a total of 62 damage on a perfect hit.<br><br>Now, if this weapon was 22 damage 20 delay (adding in the damage bonus to the ratio) I would be dealing about 100 points of damage or more per hit. the change is obvious, and this is why damage bonus isn't factored into the ratio<br><br>Bane damage is added to the ratio as stated, damage 'bonus' is just that... an additional few bonus points of damage after the damage from the ratio has been done.<br><br>Hopefully that helps clear things up a bit, but since I see this so often it kinda gets on my nerves and I had to say something :) If I left anything out feel free to fill in the gaps.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Oct 24 21:14:46 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Harik Honorblade<br>56th Dwarven Myrmidon<br>Esuna Emberfist<br>45th Human Monk</td></tr>
